# Valve gripper turn command/configuration (see gripper_roll_tracker.py).
#
# direction: "cw" or "ccw" — the sense the valve HANDLE turns, as seen by an
#            observer facing the valve face (for the bottom valve: looking
#            down at it). The per-gripper mapping from this convention to the
#            servo sign is the tracker's ~ccw_sign parameter.
#
# Used by two services:
#   rotate             — degrees: how far to turn (> 0). Latches the current
#                        tracked roll, ramps to (latched ± degrees), holds.
#                        Blocks until the ramp completes.
#   set_turn_direction — degrees: required headroom (0 → keep current, default
#                        90). Tracking then always parks the servo on a branch
#                        with at least this much travel in `direction`.
string direction
float64 degrees
---
bool success
string message
